<TITLE> HC suspends MP Alamgir's sentence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com)The High Court Thursday suspended for four months the sentence the sentence of Awami League MP MK Alamgir, given in an illegal wealth case. A HC bench of justices Md Muzammel Hossain and Md Afzal Hossain Ahmed passed the order on a petition by Alamgir. A Dhaka Special Court sentenced the AL leader to 13 years imprisonment on July 27, 2007 in the case filed by the Anticorruption Commission for amassing illegal wealth and concealment of wealth information. Barrister Rafique-ul-Haque moved the petition for Alamgir, while senior advocate Khan Saifur Rahman opposed on behalf of the ACC. Alamgir was earlier released on HC bail in the case. A separate HC bench, of justices Mir Hasmat Ali and Shamim Hasnain, directed the government and bank authorities to permit former law minister Moudud Ahmed to withdraw up to Tk 5 lakh from his bank account per month on a petition. Moudud himself moved the petition, while deputy attorney general Zafar Imam opposed it. The HC earlier directed the government and banking authorities to permit him to withdraw up to Tk 1.25 lakh per month. Moudud's bank account was frozen by the immediate past caretaker government. 
